  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Light is the primary means by which the internal circadian clock remains aligned
      (&quot;entrained&quot;) with the external world. Misalignment of this internal clock can occur during
      situations such as shift work and jet travel across multiple time zones (jet lag). The
      purpose of this study is to examine the parameters of light and how they affect entrainment
      of the clock.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
